recent_articles.title: Apple Q3 earnings top estimates, iPhone sales give results a boost
recent_articles.summary:
Apple (AAPL) reported fiscal third quarter results that topped Wall Street estimates on both the top and bottom lines. Earnings of $1.57 per share topped the Bloomberg consensus estimate of $1.43. Revenue of $94.04 billion was better than the expected $89.30 billion. Mac and iPhone revenue were both better than analysts had anticipated, while wearables and iPad numbers fell short. Greater China revenue was $15.37 billion versus an estimate of $15.19 billion.
